We usually describe light–matter interaction in a linear response manner;
 the electromagnetic (EM) field is considered a perturbation to the matter
 system and the optical response are predicted by extrapolating the behavior
 of the system.
 This scheme does not not account for the feedback of the matter system
 toward the EM field.
 
