In order to study the steady state of non-equilibrium dynamics, we introduce
 a non-radiative dissipation among the vibrational modes of the ground state.
 We know that, in absence of the external CW field, the ground state population
 of different vibrational modes should follow Boltzmann distribution and
 the dissipative transition rate must be
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\overline{\rho_{00}}}{\overline{\rho_{11}}}=\frac{\gamma_{0\leftarrow1}}{\gamma_{1\leftarrow0}}=\frac{e^{-\beta\varepsilon_{0}}}{e^{-\beta\varepsilon_{1}}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=1/kT$
\end_inset

