In this work, we develop the framework of mixed quantum–classical theory
 for coupled electron-radiation dynamics in terms of electrodynamical QLCE
 and Ehrenfest EOM formulation.
 With the understanding and explicit analysis, we propose an ad hoc Ehrenfest+R
 method by introducing the complementary quantum transitions to recover
 the deficiency of the standard Ehrenfest dynamics.
 In the context of spontaneous emission, Ehrenfest+R dynamics predict the
 correct decay rate and discriminate the coherent and incoherent emission
 intensity in a great agreement with full quantum results.
 Furthermore, we generalize Ehrenfest+R method to treat a resonance Raman
 scattering model and demonstrate its capability of capturing quantitative
 results of resonance spectra and linewidth.
